British Printing and CommunicationCorporation Plc &lt;BPCL.L> has proposed the cancellation of allits preference shares in return for cash payments totalling14.8 mln stg.    BPCC said in a statement, "In view of the enlarged ordinaryshare capital and the improved financial position of thecompany, the Board considers that the relatively small amountof preference share capital now represents capital in excess ofthe company's wants."    Shareholder approval will be sought at a meeeting onNovember 10.If granted, court confirmation will be required. REUTER&#3;